<subSubSection id="1BAB4268842123129722229CB540DDB3" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="9742E1F542FE4E8462002F56302ED8B0" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DB78D35A29DC32582B32364314578DE9" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
<taxonomicName id="D85CD5FCD5A2A4D7310411494D5EC75E" authorityName="Schiodte" authorityYear="1849" class="Arachnida" family="Liphistiidae" genus="Liphistius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Liphistius" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CAA55E5AF6B824D5463AD808CAA5F4C3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Liphistius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the other seven liphistiid genera by the presence of signal lines radiating from the 
<normalizedToken id="04A6F050BD095249E932316638B3AB52" originalValue="burrow’s">burrow's</normalizedToken>
entrance (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="27BDD247FCCE52B1C3C341A1717BAE19" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Microhabitat, burrows, and general somatic morphology of three new Liphistius species A microhabitat B burrow with trapdoor closed C same, trapdoor opened D male, L. hatyai Zhan &amp; Xu, sp. nov (XUX- 2017 - 492) E female, L. inthanon Zhan &amp; Xu, sp. nov. (XUX- 2017 - 374) F male, L. keeratikiati Zhan &amp; Xu, sp. nov. (XUX- 2017 - 435) Scale bars: 5 mm (D, E, F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1104.83264.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/694474" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">1B, C</figureCitation>
), by the male palp having a tibial apophysis (Figs 
<figureCitation id="B10C513B37E1415A75A3A55505000626" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Male palp and female genitalia of Liphistius hatyai Zhan &amp; Xu, sp. nov. A palp, prolateral view B palp, ventral view C palp, retrolateral view D-G palp, distal views H vulva, dorsal view I vulva, ventral view A-G XUX- 2017 - 492 (holotype) H, I XUX- 2017 - 493. Abbreviations used: CDO = central dorsal opening; GA = genital atrium; PS = posterior stalk; RC = receptacular cluster; CT = contrategulum; Cu = cumulus; PC = paracymbium; PeP = paraembolic plate; ST = subtegulum; T = tegulum; TiA = tibial apophysis. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1104.83264.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/694476" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">3A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="A1F5C4E1540B5438CFAFE950A0BFF8E8" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Male palp and female genitalia of Liphistius inthanon Zhan &amp; Xu, sp. nov. A palp, prolateral view B palp, ventral view C palp, retrolateral view D-G palp, distal views H-J vulva, dorsal view K-M vulva, ventral view A-C XUX- 2017 - 372 A (holotype) D-G XUX- 2017 - 373 A H, K XUX- 2017 - 372 I, L XUX- 2017 - 379 J, M XUX- 2017 - 381. Abbreviations used: CDO = central dorsal opening; GA = genital atrium; RC = receptacular cluster; CT = contrategulum; Cu = cumulus; E = embolus; PC = paracymbium; PeP = paraembolic plate; ST = subtegulum; T = tegulum; TiA = tibial apophysis. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1104.83264.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/694477" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">4A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="9996EC8D8B215CA4F09A6016134995FF" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Male palp and female genitalia of Liphistius keeratikiati Zhan &amp; Xu, sp. nov. A palp, prolateral view B palp, ventral view C palp, retrolateral view D-G palp, distal views H vulva, dorsal view I vulva, ventral view J vulva, lateral view A-G XUX- 2017 - 439 (holotype) H-J XUX- 2017 - 431. Abbreviations used: CDO = central dorsal opening; GA = genital atrium; RC = receptacular cluster; CT = contrategulum; Cu = cumulus; E = embolus; PC = paracymbium; PeP = paraembolic plate; ST = subtegulum; T = tegulum; TiA = tibial apophysis. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1104.83264.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/694478" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">5A</figureCitation>
), and by the female genitalia having a sclerotized poreplate and a median receptacular cluster (Figs 
<figureCitation id="3C71D3CF6C98E4C05312E6665382F723" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Male palp and female genitalia of Liphistius hatyai Zhan &amp; Xu, sp. nov. A palp, prolateral view B palp, ventral view C palp, retrolateral view D-G palp, distal views H vulva, dorsal view I vulva, ventral view A-G XUX- 2017 - 492 (holotype) H, I XUX- 2017 - 493. Abbreviations used: CDO = central dorsal opening; GA = genital atrium; PS = posterior stalk; RC = receptacular cluster; CT = contrategulum; Cu = cumulus; PC = paracymbium; PeP = paraembolic plate; ST = subtegulum; T = tegulum; TiA = tibial apophysis. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1104.83264.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/694476" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">3H-I</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="1FE058445770BED4025E7CDADE3E4BFF" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Male palp and female genitalia of Liphistius inthanon Zhan &amp; Xu, sp. nov. A palp, prolateral view B palp, ventral view C palp, retrolateral view D-G palp, distal views H-J vulva, dorsal view K-M vulva, ventral view A-C XUX- 2017 - 372 A (holotype) D-G XUX- 2017 - 373 A H, K XUX- 2017 - 372 I, L XUX- 2017 - 379 J, M XUX- 2017 - 381. Abbreviations used: CDO = central dorsal opening; GA = genital atrium; RC = receptacular cluster; CT = contrategulum; Cu = cumulus; E = embolus; PC = paracymbium; PeP = paraembolic plate; ST = subtegulum; T = tegulum; TiA = tibial apophysis. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1104.83264.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/694477" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">4H-M</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="81F9C99F6FC8D9910A9025B8F130C8CD" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Male palp and female genitalia of Liphistius keeratikiati Zhan &amp; Xu, sp. nov. A palp, prolateral view B palp, ventral view C palp, retrolateral view D-G palp, distal views H vulva, dorsal view I vulva, ventral view J vulva, lateral view A-G XUX- 2017 - 439 (holotype) H-J XUX- 2017 - 431. Abbreviations used: CDO = central dorsal opening; GA = genital atrium; RC = receptacular cluster; CT = contrategulum; Cu = cumulus; E = embolus; PC = paracymbium; PeP = paraembolic plate; ST = subtegulum; T = tegulum; TiA = tibial apophysis. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1104.83264.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/694478" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">5H-J</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="D5FB0025EDABFE0105C0595CF98E2A22" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1104.83264.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/694476" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" start="Figure 3" startId="F3">
